whispSmMibModule.name: whispSmMibModule
whispSmMibModule.description: This module contains MIB definitions for Subscriber Modem.

rfScanList.name: rfScanList
rfScanList.description: RF scan list string. The frequencies vary by product and region. If the list is too long an SNMP error will be returned. If this occurs please refer to OID rfScanListTable, which will allow user to enter the full range of available frequencies. Special settings: 0: none. all: All frequencies in the band(s) supported by the radio will be selected. all49, all51, all52: Available only for 450i 5 GHz wideband radio. all54, all57: Available only for 450 and 450i 5 GHz radios. When doing a set, separate values with comma with no white space between values.

powerUpMode.name: powerUpMode
powerUpMode.description: SM Power Up Mode With No 802.3 Link. 1 -- Power up in Aim mode 2 -- Power up in Operational mode.

networkAccess.name: networkAccess
networkAccess.description: Network accessibility. Public or local IP. For multipoint only.

authKeySm.name: authKeySm
authKeySm.description: Authentication key. It should be equal or less than 32 characters long.

enable8023link.name: enable8023link
enable8023link.description: To enable or disable 802.3 link. For SMs only.

authKeyOption.name: authKeyOption
authKeyOption.description: This option is for SMs only. Backhaul timing slave always uses the set key. 0 - Use default key. 1 - Use set key.

timingPulseGated.name: timingPulseGated
timingPulseGated.description: 0 - Disable (Always propagate the frame timing pulse). 1 - Enable (If SM out of sync then dont propagate the frame timing pulse).

naptPrivateIP.name: naptPrivateIP
naptPrivateIP.description: NAPT private IP address. Only the first three bytes can be changed when NAPT is enabled.

naptPrivateSubnetMask.name: naptPrivateSubnetMask
naptPrivateSubnetMask.description: NAPT private subnet mask. Only the last byte can be changed when NAPT is enabled. The address will always be: 255.255.255.x.

naptPublicIP.name: naptPublicIP
naptPublicIP.description: IP Address of NAPT Public Interface. The variable is available only when NAPT is enabled.

naptPublicSubnetMask.name: naptPublicSubnetMask
naptPublicSubnetMask.description: Subnet mask for NAPT Public Interface. The variable is available only when NAPT is enabled.

naptPublicGatewayIP.name: naptPublicGatewayIP
naptPublicGatewayIP.description: IP Address of NAPT Public Interface Gateway. The variable is available only when NAPT is enabled.

naptRFPublicIP.name: naptRFPublicIP
naptRFPublicIP.description: IP Address of RF Public Interface. The variable is available only when NAPT is enabled.

naptRFPublicSubnetMask.name: naptRFPublicSubnetMask
naptRFPublicSubnetMask.description: Subnet mask of RF Public Interface. The variable is available only when NAPT is enabled.

naptRFPublicGateway.name: naptRFPublicGateway
naptRFPublicGateway.description: IP Address of RF Public Interface Gateway. The variable is available only when NAPT is enabled.

naptEnable.name: naptEnable
naptEnable.description: To enable or disable NAPT. For multipoint only. 1=Enable NAPT, 0=Disable NAPT.

arpCacheTimeout.name: arpCacheTimeout
arpCacheTimeout.description: ARP cache time out in unit of minutes. For multipoint only. Range from 1-30.

tcpGarbageCollectTmout.name: tcpGarbageCollectTmout
tcpGarbageCollectTmout.description: Units of minutes for TCP garbage collection. For multipoint only. Range 4-1440.

udpGarbageCollectTmout.name: udpGarbageCollectTmout
udpGarbageCollectTmout.description: Units of minutes for UDP garbage collection. For multipoint only. Range 1-1440.

dhcpClientEnable.name: dhcpClientEnable
dhcpClientEnable.description: To enable or disable DHCP client. For multipoint SM's with NAPT enabled.

dhcpServerEnable.name: dhcpServerEnable
dhcpServerEnable.description: To enable or disable DHCP server. For multipoint SM's with NAPT enabled.

dhcpServerLeaseTime.name: dhcpServerLeaseTime
dhcpServerLeaseTime.description: Units of days for DHCP server lease time. For multipoint SM's with NAPT enabled. Range from 1-30.

dhcpIPStart.name: dhcpIPStart
dhcpIPStart.description: The last byte will be set for the starting IP that our DHCP server gives away. The first 3 bytes of the starting IP are the same as those of NAPT private IP

dnsAutomatic.name: dnsAutomatic
dnsAutomatic.description: To have DHCP Server obtain DNS information automatically or manually.

prefferedDNSIP.name: prefferedDNSIP
prefferedDNSIP.description: The preferred DNS IP when we are configured for static DNS (Not used when configured for automatic DNS).

alternateDNSIP.name: alternateDNSIP
alternateDNSIP.description: The alternate DNS IP when we are configured for static DNS (Not used when configured for automatic DNS).

dmzIP.name: dmzIP
dmzIP.description: Only the last byte of DMZ Host IP will be set. The first 3 bytes of DMZ IP are the same as those of NAPT private IP.

dmzEnable.name: dmzEnable
dmzEnable.description: To enable or disable DMZ host functionality.

dhcpNumIPsToLease.name: dhcpNumIPsToLease
dhcpNumIPsToLease.description: Number of IP addresses that our DHCP server can give away.

pppoeFilter.name: pppoeFilter
pppoeFilter.description: To set PPPoE packet filter when NAT is disabled. Obsolete - Use corresponding OID in whipsBoxConfig MIB.

smbFilter.name: smbFilter
smbFilter.description: To set SMB packet filter when NAT is disabled. Obsolete - Use corresponding OID in whipsBoxConfig MIB.

snmpFilter.name: snmpFilter
snmpFilter.description: To set SNMP packet filter when NAT is disabled. Obsolete - Use corresponding OID in whipsBoxConfig MIB.

userP1Filter.name: userP1Filter
userP1Filter.description: To set user defined port 1 packet filter when NAT is disabled. Obsolete - Use corresponding OID in whipsBoxConfig MIB.

userP2Filter.name: userP2Filter
userP2Filter.description: To set user defined port 2 packet filter when NAT is disabled. Obsolete - Use corresponding OID in whipsBoxConfig MIB.

userP3Filter.name: userP3Filter
userP3Filter.description: To set user defined port 3 packet filter when NAT is disabled. Obsolete - Use corresponding OID in whipsBoxConfig MIB.

allOtherIpFilter.name: allOtherIpFilter
allOtherIpFilter.description: To set all other IPv4 packet filter when NAT is disabled. Obsolete - Use corresponding OID in whipsBoxConfig MIB.

arpFilter.name: arpFilter
arpFilter.description: To set ARP packet filter when NAT is disabled. Obsolete - Use corresponding OID in whipsBoxConfig MIB.

allOthersFilter.name: allOthersFilter
allOthersFilter.description: To set all other packet filter when NAT is disabled. Obsolete - Use corresponding OID in whipsBoxConfig MIB.

userDefinedPort1.name: userDefinedPort1
userDefinedPort1.description: An integer value of number one user defined port. Range:0-65535 Obsolete - Use corresponding OID in whipsBoxConfig MIB.

port1TCPFilter.name: port1TCPFilter
port1TCPFilter.description: To set user defined port 1 TCP traffic filter. Obsolete - Use corresponding OID in whipsBoxConfig MIB.

port1UDPFilter.name: port1UDPFilter
port1UDPFilter.description: To set user defined port 1 UDP traffic filter. Obsolete - Use corresponding OID in whipsBoxConfig MIB.

userDefinedPort2.name: userDefinedPort2
userDefinedPort2.description: An integer value of number two user defined port. Range:0-65535 Obsolete - Use corresponding OID in whipsBoxConfig MIB.

port2TCPFilter.name: port2TCPFilter
port2TCPFilter.description: To set user defined port 2 TCP traffic filter. Obsolete - Use corresponding OID in whipsBoxConfig MIB.

port2UDPFilter.name: port2UDPFilter
port2UDPFilter.description: To set user defined port 2 UDP traffic filter. Obsolete - Use corresponding OID in whipsBoxConfig MIB.

userDefinedPort3.name: userDefinedPort3
userDefinedPort3.description: An integer value of number three user defined port. Range:0-65535 Obsolete - Use corresponding OID in whipsBoxConfig MIB.

port3TCPFilter.name: port3TCPFilter
port3TCPFilter.description: To set user defined port 3 TCP traffic filter. Obsolete - Use corresponding OID in whipsBoxConfig MIB.

port3UDPFilter.name: port3UDPFilter
port3UDPFilter.description: To set user defined port 3 UDP traffic filter. Obsolete - Use corresponding OID in whipsBoxConfig MIB.

bootpcFilter.name: bootpcFilter
bootpcFilter.description: To set bootp client sourced packets filter when NAT is disabled. Obsolete - Use corresponding OID in whipsBoxConfig MIB.

bootpsFilter.name: bootpsFilter
bootpsFilter.description: To set bootp server sourced packets filter when NAT is disabled. Obsolete - Use corresponding OID in whipsBoxConfig MIB.

ip4MultFilter.name: ip4MultFilter
ip4MultFilter.description: To set IPv4 MultiCast packets filter when NAT is disabled. Obsolete - Use corresponding OID in whipsBoxConfig MIB.

hiPriorityChannel.name: hiPriorityChannel
hiPriorityChannel.description: To enable or disable high priority channel.

smRateAdapt.name: smRateAdapt
smRateAdapt.description: Rate adaptation parameter. 0: no rate adaptation. 1: 1x and 2x adaptation. 2: 1x,2x and 3x adaptation.

dfsConfig.name: dfsConfig
dfsConfig.description: To configure proper regions for Dynamic Frequency Shifting. For 5.2/5.4/5.7 GHz radios.

ethAccessFilterEnable.name: ethAccessFilterEnable
ethAccessFilterEnable.description: To enable or disable Ethernet Port access filtering to SM Management Functions. (0) - Ethernet access to SM Management allowed. (1) - Ethernet access to SM Management blocked.

ipAccessFilterEnable.name: ipAccessFilterEnable
ipAccessFilterEnable.description: To enable or disable IP access filtering to Management functions. (0) - IP access will be allowed from all addresses. (1) - IP access will be controlled using allowedIPAccess1-3 entries.

allowedIPAccess1.name: allowedIPAccess1
allowedIPAccess1.description: Allow access to SM Management from this IP. 0 is default setting to allow from all IPs.

allowedIPAccess2.name: allowedIPAccess2
allowedIPAccess2.description: Allow access to SM Management from this IP. 0 is default setting to allow from all IPs.

allowedIPAccess3.name: allowedIPAccess3
allowedIPAccess3.description: Allow access to SM Management from this IP. 0 is default setting to allow from all IPs.

rfDhcpState.name: rfDhcpState
rfDhcpState.description: To enable or disable RF Interface DHCP feature.

bCastMIR.name: bCastMIR
bCastMIR.description: To enable and set Broadcast/ Multicast MIR feature. Use value of 0 to disable. Units are as per bCastMIRUnits variable. Set the units first and then set this value.

bhsReReg.name: bhsReReg
bhsReReg.description: Allows BHS re-registration every 24 hours. Enable allows re-registration and Disable does not. 24 Hour Encryption Refresh.

smLEDModeFlag.name: smLEDModeFlag
smLEDModeFlag.description: To set LED Panel Operation to Revised Mode(1) or to Legacy Mode(0)

ethAccessEnable.name: ethAccessEnable
ethAccessEnable.description: To enable or disable Ethernet Port access to SM Management Functions. (1) - Ethernet access to SM Management allowed. (0) - Ethernet access to SM Management blocked.

pppoeEnable.name: pppoeEnable
pppoeEnable.description: Enable or disable PPPoE on the SM. NAT MUST be enabled prior and Translation Bridging MUST be DISABLED on the AP.

pppoeAuthenticationType.name: pppoeAuthenticationType
pppoeAuthenticationType.description: Set the PPPoE Authentication Type to either None or CHAP/pap

pppoeAccessConcentrator.name: pppoeAccessConcentrator
pppoeAccessConcentrator.description: Set the PPPoE Access Concentrator Name. Less than or equal to 32 characters

pppoeServiceName.name: pppoeServiceName
pppoeServiceName.description: Set the PPPoE Service Name. Less than or equal to 32 characters

pppoeUserName.name: pppoeUserName
pppoeUserName.description: Set the PPPoE Username. Less than or equal to 32 characters

pppoePassword.name: pppoePassword
pppoePassword.description: Set the PPPoE Password. Less than or equal to 32 characters

pppoeTCPMSSClampEnable.name: pppoeTCPMSSClampEnable
pppoeTCPMSSClampEnable.description: Enable or disable TCP MSS Clamping. Enabling this will cause the SM to edit the TCP MSS in TCP SYN and SYN-ACK packets. This will allow for a workaround for MTU issues so that the TCP session will only go up to the clamped MSS. If you are using PMTUD reliably, this should not be needed.

pppoeMTUOverrideEnable.name: pppoeMTUOverrideEnable
pppoeMTUOverrideEnable.description: Enable the overriding of the PPP link's MTU. Normally, the PPP link will set the MTU to the MRU of the PPPoE Server, but this may be overridden. If the MRU of the PPPoE server is smaller than the desired MTU, the smaller MTU will be used.

pppoeMTUOverrideValue.name: pppoeMTUOverrideValue
pppoeMTUOverrideValue.description: Enable the overriding of the PPP link's MTU. Normally, the PPP link will set the MTU to the MRU of the PPPoE Server, but this may be overridden. If the MRU of the PPPoE server is smaller than the desired MTU, the smaller MTU will be used. Max MTU of a PPPoE link is 1492.

pppoeTimerType.name: pppoeTimerType
pppoeTimerType.description: Set the PPPoE Timer type. Can be a Keep Alive timer where the link will be checked periodically and automatically redialed if the link is down. Also could be an Idle Timeout where the link will be automatically dropped after an idle period and redialed if user data is present. Keep Alive timers are in seconds while Idle Timeout timers are in minutes.

pppoeTimeoutPeriod.name: pppoeTimeoutPeriod
pppoeTimeoutPeriod.description: The Timeout Period. The use of this depends on the Timer Type. If the Timer Type is KeepAlive, then the timeout period is in seconds. If the Timer Type is Idle Timeout, then the timeout period is in minutes. Minimum values are 20 seconds for KeepAlive timer, and 5 minutes for Idle Timeout.

timedSpectrumAnalysisDuration.name: timedSpectrumAnalysisDuration
timedSpectrumAnalysisDuration.description: As of release 13.0.2 this value is depricated. Please use the OID in whispBoxConfig. Value in seconds for a timed spectrum analysis. Range is 10-1000 seconds.

spectrumAnalysisOnBoot.name: spectrumAnalysisOnBoot
spectrumAnalysisOnBoot.description: To enable or disable Spectrum Analysis on boot up for one scan through the band. (0) - Disabled (1) - Enabled

spectrumAnalysisAction.name: spectrumAnalysisAction
spectrumAnalysisAction.description: As of release 13.0.2, this OID has been deprecated. Please use the OID in whispBoxConfig. Start or stop timed or continuous Spectrum Analysis and also give status. (0) - Stop Spectrum Analysis (1) - Start Timed Spectrum Analysis (2) - Start Continuous Spectrum Analysis (3) - Idle, no Spectrum Analysis results. (4) - Idle, Spectrum Analysis results available. (5) - Timed or Remote Spectrum Analysis in progress. (6) - Continuous Spectrum Analysis in progress. Note: Continuous mode has a max of 24 hours.

pppoeConnectOD.name: pppoeConnectOD
pppoeConnectOD.description: Force a manual PPPoE connection attempt.

smAntennaType.name: smAntennaType
smAntennaType.description: Deprecated. See whispBoxStatus.antType for antenna type information.

natConnectionType.name: natConnectionType
natConnectionType.description: To configure the SM NAT connection type. Options are Static IP, DHCP, or PPPoE.

wanPingReplyEnable.name: wanPingReplyEnable
wanPingReplyEnable.description: Allow Ping replies from SM WAN interface. Applies to both NAT and PPPoE WAN interfaces.

packetFilterDirection.name: packetFilterDirection
packetFilterDirection.description: To packet filter direction when NAT is disabled. Upstream is default. Obsolete - Use corresponding OID in whipsBoxConfig MIB.

colorCode2.name: colorCode2
colorCode2.description: Second Color code. The variable is deprecated. See additionalColorCode in whispSmConfig.

colorCodepriority2.name: colorCodepriority2
colorCodepriority2.description: Priority setting for the second color code. The variable is deprecated. See additionalColorCodePriority in whispSmConfig.

colorCode3.name: colorCode3
colorCode3.description: Third Color code. The variable is deprecated. See additionalColorCode in whispSmConfig.

colorCodepriority3.name: colorCodepriority3
colorCodepriority3.description: Priority setting for the third color code. The variable is deprecated. See additionalColorCodePriority in whispSmConfig.

colorCode4.name: colorCode4
colorCode4.description: Fourth Color code. The variable is deprecated. See additionalColorCode in whispSmConfig.

colorCodepriority4.name: colorCodepriority4
colorCodepriority4.description: Priority setting for the fourth color code. The variable is deprecated. See additionalColorCodePriority in whispSmConfig.

colorCode5.name: colorCode5
colorCode5.description: Fifth Color code. The variable is deprecated. See additionalColorCode in whispSmConfig.

colorCodepriority5.name: colorCodepriority5
colorCodepriority5.description: Priority setting for the fifth color code. The variable is deprecated. See additionalColorCodePriority in whispSmConfig.

colorCode6.name: colorCode6
colorCode6.description: Sixth Color code. The variable is deprecated. See additionalColorCode in whispSmConfig.

colorCodepriority6.name: colorCodepriority6
colorCodepriority6.description: Priority setting for the sixth color code. The variable is deprecated. See additionalColorCodePriority in whispSmConfig.

colorCode7.name: colorCode7
colorCode7.description: Seventh Color code. The variable is deprecated. See additionalColorCode in whispSmConfig.

colorCodepriority7.name: colorCodepriority7
colorCodepriority7.description: Priority setting for the seventh color code. The variable is deprecated. See additionalColorCodePriority in whispSmConfig.

colorCode8.name: colorCode8
colorCode8.description: Eighth Color code. The variable is deprecated. See additionalColorCode in whispSmConfig.

colorCodepriority8.name: colorCodepriority8
colorCodepriority8.description: Priority setting for the eighth color code. The variable is deprecated. See additionalColorCodePriority in whispSmConfig.

colorCode9.name: colorCode9
colorCode9.description: Ninth Color code. The variable is deprecated. See additionalColorCode in whispSmConfig.

colorCodepriority9.name: colorCodepriority9
colorCodepriority9.description: Priority setting for the ninth color code. The variable is deprecated. See additionalColorCodePriority in whispSmConfig.

colorCode10.name: colorCode10
colorCode10.description: Tenth Color code. The variable is deprecated. See additionalColorCode in whispSmConfig.

colorCodepriority10.name: colorCodepriority10
colorCodepriority10.description: Priority setting for the tenth color code. The variable is deprecated. See additionalColorCodePriority in whispSmConfig.

natDNSProxyEnable.name: natDNSProxyEnable
natDNSProxyEnable.description: If enabled, the SM will advertise itself as the DNS server when it sends out DHCP client leases and forward DNS queries automatically. If disabled, the SM will forward on upstream DNS server information when it sends out DHCP client leases.

allIpv4Filter.name: allIpv4Filter
allIpv4Filter.description: To set all IPv4 packet filter when NAT is disabled. Enabling this will automatically enable all of the known IP filters (SMB, SNMP, Bootp, IPv4 Mcast, User Defined Ports, and All Other IPv4). Obsolete - Use corresponding OID in whipsBoxConfig MIB.

spectrumAnalysisDisplay.name: spectrumAnalysisDisplay
spectrumAnalysisDisplay.description: The display for Spectrum Analyzer: (0) - Averaging over entire period (1) - Instantaneous showing the last reading

syslogSMXmitSetting.name: syslogSMXmitSetting
syslogSMXmitSetting.description: Obtains Syslog transmit configuration from AP/BHM if set to 0, overrides if 1 or 2. Transmits syslog data to Syslog server if enabled(1), stops if disabled (2).

syslogServerApPreferred.name: syslogServerApPreferred
syslogServerApPreferred.description: Uses Syslog server configuration from AP/BHM if enabled and available, otherwise uses local configuration.

syslogMinLevelApPreferred.name: syslogMinLevelApPreferred
syslogMinLevelApPreferred.description: Uses Syslog minimum transmit level configuration from AP/BHM if available, otherwise uses local configuration.

syslogSMXmitControl.name: syslogSMXmitControl
syslogSMXmitControl.description: Obtains Syslog transmit configuration from AP/BHM if available, or specifies the local transmit state.

eapPeerAAAServerCommonName.name: eapPeerAAAServerCommonName
eapPeerAAAServerCommonName.description: THIS OID IS CURRENTLY UNUSED: EAP Peer Server Common Name

cyclicPrefixScan.name: cyclicPrefixScan
cyclicPrefixScan.description: Cyclic Prefix value for frequency scanning used by MIMO SMs only. When setting use a comma delimited list of cyclic prefixes with no spaces. For example: 1/8,1/16

bandwidthScan.name: bandwidthScan
bandwidthScan.description: Bandwidth values for frequency scanning used by MIMO SMs only. When setting use a comma delimited list of bandwidths. For example: 10, 20

apSelection.name: apSelection
apSelection.description: This OID affects what AP to attempt to register to when Canopy SMs scan see more than one AP that are valid in it's configuration. (0) - Default, Canopy radios after scanning select the best AP that will optimize for estimated throughput. (1) - Select the AP with the best receive power level. Note this is only if multiple APs fit the current scan configuration, and will be overriden by color codes, RADIUS, etc.

radioBandscanConfig.name: radioBandscanConfig
radioBandscanConfig.description: Used to determine when frequency, cyclic prefix and bandwidth settings take effect for band scanning MIMO SMs. 0 - Instant 1 - Delayed 2 - Apply changes

forcepoweradjust.name: forcepoweradjust
forcepoweradjust.description: This will force a multipoint SM to initiate an asynchronous power adjust sequence. This is done automatically every 2 minutes.

clearBerrResults.name: clearBerrResults
clearBerrResults.description: This will clear the BER results.

berrautoupdateflag.name: berrautoupdateflag
berrautoupdateflag.description: This indicates if the once a second BERR updating of counters is enabled. 1 = enabled 0 = disabled

testSMBER.name: testSMBER
testSMBER.description: 0 - Disable (Return the SM to a normal operation state). 1 - Enable (Set SM into a BER test state).

allowedIPAccessNMLength1.name: allowedIPAccessNMLength1
allowedIPAccessNMLength1.description: Length of the network mask to apply to the AllowedIPAddress when assessing if access is allowed

allowedIPAccessNMLength2.name: allowedIPAccessNMLength2
allowedIPAccessNMLength2.description: Length of the network mask to apply to the AllowedIPAddress when assessing if access is allowed

allowedIPAccessNMLength3.name: allowedIPAccessNMLength3
allowedIPAccessNMLength3.description: Length of the network mask to apply to the AllowedIPAddress when assessing if access is allowed

naptRemoteManage.name: naptRemoteManage
naptRemoteManage.description: To enable or disable Remote Management. For multipoint only. 0=Disable Remote Management, 1=Enable - Standalone Config, 2=Enable - Use WAN Interface.

spectrumAnalysisScanBandwidth.name: spectrumAnalysisScanBandwidth
spectrumAnalysisScanBandwidth.description: Scanning Bandwidth used for the Spectrum Analyzer. Only available on PMP 450.

berDeModSelect.name: berDeModSelect
berDeModSelect.description: The BER demodulation level the SM is set. 0 for QPSK, 1 for 16-QAM, 2 for 64-QAM, and 3 for 256-QAM.

pmp430ApRegistrationOptions.name: pmp430ApRegistrationOptions
pmp430ApRegistrationOptions.description: Selects AP types (PMP 430 and/or PMP 450/450i) that are available for the PMP 430 SM. When both AP types are selected, if the SM does not register to an AP after 10 minutes, it will reboot to scan the other AP type.

switchRadioModeAndReboot.name: switchRadioModeAndReboot
switchRadioModeAndReboot.description: Setting this to 1 will force switch the SM to the other radio mode and immediately reboot the unit. When the unit finishes rebooting, it will be in finishedReboot state. Only will be allowed to be set if both registration options are configured. PMP 430 SM only. Introduced in release 12.2.

additionalColorCode.name: additionalColorCode
additionalColorCode.description: Add an additional color code. Setting additionalColorCode and additionalColorCodePriority adds an entry.

additionalColorCodePriority.name: additionalColorCodePriority
additionalColorCodePriority.description: Add an additional color code priority. Setting additionalColorCode and additionalColorCodePriority adds an entry.

bCastMIRUnits.name: bCastMIRUnits
bCastMIRUnits.description: Units of Broadcast/ Multicast MIR value. Set units first and then bCastMIR

rfScanListTable.name: rfScanListTable
rfScanListTable.description: The list of configured scanning frequencies on the SM or BHS.

rfScanListEntry.name: rfScanListEntry
rfScanListEntry.description: Entry of configured scanning frequencies on the SM or BHS.

rfScanListFrequency.name: rfScanListFrequency
rfScanListFrequency.description: RF scan list. The frequencies vary by product and region.

numAuthCerts.name: numAuthCerts
numAuthCerts.description: can have a max value of 2

authenticationEnforce.name: authenticationEnforce
authenticationEnforce.description: enforce SM to register with specifed Auth Enabled AP

phase1.name: phase1
phase1.description: Select the outer method for EAP Authentication. Note: PEAP is not supported for MPC860 platform.

phase2.name: phase2
phase2.description: Select the outer method for EAP Authentication

useRealm.name: useRealm
useRealm.description: Enable or disable the use of realm option.

certTable.name: certTable
certTable.description: The table of CA Certificates on SM.

rssi.name: rssi
rssi.description: Radio signal strength index. FSK only.

jitter.name: jitter
jitter.description: A measure of multipath interference. Applicable to FSK radios only.

radioTxGainSm.name: radioTxGainSm
radioTxGainSm.description: Radio transmission gain setting. Applicable to FSK radios only.

radioDbm.name: radioDbm
radioDbm.description: Rx Power level. For MIMO this is the combined power of the horizontal and vertical paths.

registeredToAp.name: registeredToAp
registeredToAp.description: AP MAC address that the SM registered to.

dhcpCip.name: dhcpCip
dhcpCip.description: Assigned IP address to DHCP client.

radioDbmInt.name: radioDbmInt
radioDbmInt.description: Radio power level(integer). For MIMO radios this is the combined power of the horiztontal and vertical paths.

dfsStatus.name: dfsStatus
dfsStatus.description: Dynamic frequency shifting status. For DFS Radio only.

radioTxPwr.name: radioTxPwr
radioTxPwr.description: Tx Power level. Valid for FSK and OFDM SMs.

activeRegion.name: activeRegion
activeRegion.description: The active region of the radio.

snmpBerLevel.name: snmpBerLevel
snmpBerLevel.description: BER level. For PMP 450 systems: 2=MIMO QPSK, 4=MIMO 16-QAM, 6=MIMO64-QAM, 8=256-QAM For non PMP 450: 2=2 level BER, 4=4 level BER.

nbBitsRcvd.name: nbBitsRcvd
nbBitsRcvd.description: Number of BER bits received (non MIMO platforms only).

nbPriBitsErr.name: nbPriBitsErr
nbPriBitsErr.description: Number of Primary bit errors (non MIMO platforms only).

nbSndBitsErr.name: nbSndBitsErr
nbSndBitsErr.description: Number of secondary bit errors (non MIMO platforms only).

primaryBER.name: primaryBER
primaryBER.description: Obsoleted, invalid type to represent this data. Measured Primary Bit Error Rate.

secondaryBER.name: secondaryBER
secondaryBER.description: Obsoleted, invalid type to represent this data. Measured Secondary Bit Error Rate.

totalBER.name: totalBER
totalBER.description: Obsoleted, invalid type to represent this data. Measured Total Bit Error Rate.

minRSSI.name: minRSSI
minRSSI.description: Measured Min. RSSI. Applicable to FSK radios only.

maxRSSI.name: maxRSSI
maxRSSI.description: Measured Max. RSSI. Applicable to FSK radios only.

minJitter.name: minJitter
minJitter.description: Measured Min. Jitter. Applicable to FSK radios only.

maxJitter.name: maxJitter
maxJitter.description: Measured Max. Jitter. Applicable to FSK radios only.

pppoeTimerTypeValue.name: pppoeTimerTypeValue
pppoeTimerTypeValue.description: Current PPPoE Timer Type. 0 is disabled, 1 is Keep Alive timer, and 2 is Idle Timeout timer.

pppoeTimeoutValue.name: pppoeTimeoutValue
pppoeTimeoutValue.description: Current PPPoE Timeout Period. The use of this depends on the Timer Type. If the Timer Type is KeepAlive, then the timeout period is in seconds. If the Timer Type is Idle Timeout, then the timeout period is in minutes.

pppoeACNameStatus.name: pppoeACNameStatus
pppoeACNameStatus.description: Current PPPoE Access Concentrator In Use

pppoeSvcNameStatus.name: pppoeSvcNameStatus
pppoeSvcNameStatus.description: Current PPPoE Service Name In Use

pppoeSessUptime.name: pppoeSessUptime
pppoeSessUptime.description: Uptime of current PPPoE Session in ticks

primaryBERDisplay.name: primaryBERDisplay
primaryBERDisplay.description: Measured Primary Bit Error Rate. Non MIMO platforms only.
